==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English, from Anglo-Norman ''fertre'', from Latin ''feretrum'', from Greek ''pheretron'' and ''pherein'' 'to carry'

===Noun===
'''feretory'''

# a receptacle that [[house]]s [[relic]]s of saints
# an [[area]] of a [[church]] where relics are kept

